deck: A Daemon World divided among the Gods of Chaos
description:
The mysterious sector of Eidolon, deep in the heart of the Eye of Terror, is one of the most remote and peculiar of the daemon worlds fought upon during the Thirteenth Crusade. Divided into several continents wehere a different Chaos power reigns over each, the battlezones of Eidolon present a panoply of strange and excruciating ways to die. Its shifting landscapes defy all reason, and althought it was once a beautiful maiden world of the Eldar, it has changed so irrevocably that no real trace of its former glory exists. Nonetheless, the victories won by the forces of Order, notably the Eldar of Biel-tan, have established several enclaves of sanity in the roiling seas of possibility that characterise Eidolon. The Eldar hope that one day these islands can grow and become stable, and that eventually the secrets of Eidolon can be reclaimed. The planet was visited by Leonatos and his exiled Blood Angel brothers, who had undertaken an quest to retrieve the Sword of Belisarius, an sacred relic to their order lost by Leonatos. They pass through each of the Chaos Empires in hope of concluding their quest and these locations of note are.

  • The Sea of Blood: The Domain of Khorne, the Blood God. An ocean littered with sailing vessels of Chaos Champions fighting eternally among each other. The waters are riddled with tentacled creatures eager to claim all those who unfortunate to be thrown off board. The mightiest champion among them was a nameless Daemon Prince.
  • The Plague City of Ebolis: Capital of Nurgle, the Plague God, governed by the Daemon Prine Bubonnikus. Its a massive citadel surrounded by industrialized fumes and smog, completely deserted except for the plague-riddled inhabitants that lurk in the dark in the presence of strangers.
  • Vada, the City of Forbidden Pleasures: The Domain of Slaanesh, its a slaving city surrounded by a vast desert, where the worshipers of the Prince of Pleasure gather debase themselves and a new manner of pleasure is discovered every hour. Its governed by an nameless Daemon Princess and attended by her own harem of Daemonettes.
  • The Birthing Swamps: Domain of Tzeentch, the Changer of Ways. Its a large marsh-forest ever changing its shape and writhing with mutants everywhere. Visitants are prone to witnessing hallucinations and illusions

description:
Earfk is a small planet that first appears in Groot #4. It resembles Earth's Moon and has a small gas station presided over by the robotic attendant Mantron. Three lost Skrulls (one of whom is a navigator with a poor sense of direction named Laz) mistake it for Earth, and after apologizing they join Groot on a journey to save Rocket.

Overview

The planet itself is grey and rocky, and dotted with craters, overall resembling Earth's Moon. Two of its most prominent landmarks are a small building that resembles a gas station and a sign that reads "Welcome to Earfk".
name: Earfk
